# Dark Mode Professional Aesthetic

- Design for dark mode first while preserving accessibility and readability.
- Ensure strong contrast ratios for text, controls, and key calls to action.
- Maintain a sleek, modern visual style with restrained color accents and premium typography.
- Use subtle gradients, glow, and depth effects only where they improve hierarchy.
- Keep visual consistency across sections, cards, overlays, and navigation states.
